commit.title: Alternate syntax for ![]: VERNAC EXTEND Foo STATE MODIFYPROOF
commit.message:
Alternate syntax for ![]: VERNAC EXTEND Foo STATE MODIFYPROOF

eg ![proof] becomes STATE MODIFYPROOF

This commits still supports the old ![] and also local ![MODIFYPROOF],
so there is redundancy:
~~~
VERNAC EXTEND Foo STATE MODIFYPROOF
| ...

VERNAC EXTEND Foo
| ![MODIFYPROOF] ...

VERNAC EXTEND Foo
| ![proof] ...
~~~
with the 2 ![] forms being local to the rule and the STATE form
applying to the whole EXTEND except for the rules with a ![].

We should probably drop the 3rd one before merging (if we go with this
commit at all).
